👉 MongoDB is a NoSQL, document-oriented database that stores data in flexible, JSON-like documents instead of traditional tables, allowing high scalability and performance.


Flexible schema (no fixed structure)
Handles unstructured and nested data easily
High scalability (horizontal scaling)
Faster development (no schema design needed)
Good performance for large datasets
Easy integration with modern apps (JSON format)

User authentication systems (login/signup)
E-commerce apps (products, orders, cart data)
Social media apps (posts, comments, likes)
Real-time applications (chat apps, notifications)
Content management systems (blogs, articles)
Mobile apps backend
Big data & analytics applications
IoT applications (sensor data storage)

CRUD Operations
→ Create, Read, Update, Delete (basic operations in MongoDB)
Collections & Documents
→ Collection = like a table
→ Document = like a row (but in JSON format)
Mongoose (Important 🔥)
→ Used with Node.js to interact with MongoDB easily
Indexing
→ Improves query performance (very important in large apps)
Aggregation Framework
→ Used for complex queries (like filtering, grouping, analytics)
Replication
→ Copies data for backup and high availability
Sharding
→ Distributes data across multiple servers (for scaling)
Atlas (Cloud MongoDB)
→ You don’t need to install locally, can use MongoDB online


