What is CORS?

👉 CORS (Cross-Origin Resource Sharing) is a security feature of browsers

👉 It controls:

कौन सा frontend (origin)
किस backend (server) से data ले सकता है
🎯 Interview Answer:

👉 CORS is a browser security mechanism that restricts cross-origin requests. Without proper CORS configuration, API requests from different origins are blocked, causing errors like “Access blocked by CORS policy.”
CORS = “कौन किस server से data ले सकता है”